CRITICAL DECISION: LANGUAGE CHOICE
────────────────────────────────────
The execution engine is written in RUST. No Python, no Node.js, no exceptions.

Reason: Python GIL prevents true parallelism. Node.js has V8 GC pauses.
Rust offers: zero-cost abstractions, no garbage collector, fearless concurrency,
SIMD intrinsics, and direct control over memory layout.

However, for tooling, prototyping, and the ML pipeline, Python is acceptable.
For API key setup and one-off scripts, TypeScript with @polymarket/clob-client
is the fastest path.

