TIER 4 — DEVELOPMENT ENVIRONMENT (LOCAL)
════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

OS:          Windows 11 with WSL2 (Ubuntu 22.04 LTS)
             All Rust development happens inside WSL2.
IDE:         Cursor (VS Code fork with full-project AI context)
             Install rust-analyzer extension for LSP support.
Rust:        rustup with stable toolchain + nightly for SIMD intrinsics
             rustup target add x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu

Key WSL2 performance tips:
  1. Place code on WSL2 native filesystem (/home/...), NOT /mnt/c/
     (Windows filesystem mounts are ~10x slower for compilation)
  2. Increase WSL2 memory in .wslconfig:
     [wsl2]
     memory=16GB
     processors=8
  3. Use "code ." inside WSL2 terminal — Cursor/VSCode will use remote mode

